This article describes the setup of USB (Universal Serial Bus) controllers.

== Installation ==

=== Hardware detection ===
To choose the right driver, first detect the used USB controllers. The [[Hardware detection#lspci|lspci]] utility works nicely for this task:
{{RootCmd|lspci {{!}} grep --color -i usb}}

=== Kernel Configuration ===

See [[USB/Guide#Config_options_for_the_kernel]].

=== Portage Configuration ===
Portage knows the global [[USE flag]] <code>usb</code> for enabling support for USB in other packages:
{{FileBox|filename=/etc/portage/make.conf|lang=bash|1=
USE="... usb ..."
}}
After setting this be sure to update the system with the <code>--changed-use</code> option so the changes take effect:
{{Emerge|params+=--changed-use --deep|@world}}

=== Emerge ===
Install the {{Package|sys-apps/usbutils}} package, if it is not already installed by adding the <code>usb</code> USE flag and re-running emerged with <code>--changed-use</code>:

{{Emerge|sys-apps/usbutils}}

